{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}
'''[[Country calling code|Country Code]]: +423''' (formerly +41 75)<br>
'''[[International Call Prefix]]: 00'''<br>
'''[[Trunk Prefix]]: None

[[Liechtenstein]] previously used the [[+41|Swiss telephone numbering plan (+41)]] under area code 075 (formerly dialed as +41 75 from outside [[Switzerland]] and Liechtenstein), but in April 1999, it adopted its own international code +423, meaning that calls to and from Switzerland now require international dialing. It is dialed internationally as '''+423 xxx xx xx'''.
