{{Infobox settlement |name = Tserona Subregion |settlement_type = [[Subregions of Eritrea|Subregion]] |official_name = |other_name = |native_name = |nickname = |motto = |image_skyline = |imagesize = |image_caption = |image_flag = |flag_size = |image_seal = |seal_size = |image_shield = |shield_size = |image_blank_emblem = |blank_emblem_size = |image_map = |mapsize = 200px |map_caption = |image_map1 = |mapsize1 = 150px |map_caption1 = |pushpin_map = |pushpin_label_position = |subdivision_type = [[Countries of the world|Country]] |subdivision_name = {{flag|Eritrea}} |subdivision_type1 = [[Regions of Eritrea|Region]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Debub Region|Debub]] |subdivision_type2 = |subdivision_name2 = |seat_type = |seat = |government_type = |leader_title = |leader_name = |leader_title1 = |leader_name1 = |established_title = |established_date = |area_magnitude = |unit_pref = Imperial (metric) |area_footnotes = |area_total_km2 = |area_land_km2 = |area_water_km2 = |area_total_sq_mi = |area_land_sq_mi = |area_water_sq_mi = |area_water_percent = |area_urban_km2 = |area_urban_sq_mi = |area_metro_km2 = |area_metro_sq_mi = |population_as_of = |population_footnotes = |population_note = |population_total = |population_density_km2 = |population_density_sq_mi = |population_metro = |population_density_metro_km2 = |population_density_metro_sq_mi = |population_urban = |population_density_urban_km2 = |population_density_urban_mi2 = |timezone = GMT +3 |utc_offset = +3 |timezone_DST = |utc_offset_DST = |latd=|latm=|lats=|latNS= |longd=|longm=|longs= |longEW= |elevation_footnotes = |elevation_m = |elevation_ft = |postal_code_type = |postal_code = |area_code = |website = |footnotes = }}
'''Tserona Subregion''' is a [[Subregions of Eritrea|subregion]] in the southern [[Debub Region|Debub]] [[Regions of Eritrea|region]] of [[Eritrea]]. The area was a major battle zone during the [[Eritrean-Ethiopian War]] and has been a source of territorial dispute between Eritrea and [[Ethiopia]] about [[Tsorona-Zalambessa]].
==References== * [http://www.statoids.com/yer.html Tserona]
{{Districts of Eritrea}}
{{coord missing|Eritrea}}
[[Category:Southern Region (Eritrea)]] [[Category:Subregions of Eritrea]] [[Category:Disputed territories in Africa]] [[Category:Geography of Ethiopia]]
{{eritrea-geo-stub}}

The '''Twin Peaks''' are two sharply defined peaks, {{convert|750|m|-2}} high, standing together {{convert|1.5|mi}} north of [[Mount Taylor (Antarctica)|Mount Taylor]] and {{convert|2|mi|0}} west of the head of [[Hope Bay]] at the north-east end of the [[Antarctic Peninsula]]. They were discovered by the [[Swedish Antarctic Expedition]], 1901&ndash;04, under [[Otto Nordenskiöld]], and named by the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey]] following their survey of the area in 1946.

